Evp, Cfo at The Coca-Cola Company
Mr. Gary P. Fayard has been an Executive Vice President of The Coca-Cola Company since February 2003, and has been its Chief Financial Officer since December 1999. Mr. Fayard serves as the Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of Coca-Cola Corporation. He served as Senior Vice President of Coca-Cola Company since December 1999. He joined Coca-Cola Company in April 1994 and served as its Vice President and Controller since July 1994. Mr. Fayard served as a Partner at Ernst & Young LLP. He served 19 years with Ernst & Young, concluding his service there as Area Director of Audit Services and Area Director Of Manufacturing Services. Mr. Fayard has been a Director of Coca-Cola Enterprises Ltd. since 2001 and serves as a Director of Panamco. He also serves on the Board of the Atlanta Area Council of the Boy Scouts, The Financial Accounting Standards Advisory Council, The University of Alabama Board of Visitors and the Financial Executive Institute. He served as a Director of Coca-Cola Refreshments USA, Inc. from 2001 to October 2008. He served as a Director of Panamerican Beverages, Inc. since February 2001. He has been a Director of Coca-Cola FEMSA, S.A. de C.V. since 2003. He is a Member of the American Institute of CPAs and is participating in the American Assembly at Columbia University concerning the future of the accounting profession. Mr. Fayard is a graduate of The University of Alabama. He holds CPA from the University of Alabama.



