Gary P. Fayard 

		
		Former EVP and CFO, 

	
		 Coca-Cola Company 	

 
Last Updated: 05/19/2014 



Executive Summary
Fayard in May 2014 retired as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the Coca-Cola Company after 20 years of service with the company. Fayard spent nearly 20 years in accounting before joining Coca-Cola Company in 1994 as Vice President and Controller. He worked on the Coca-Cola engagement as a Partner with Ernst  
Personal Attributes and Interests

Fayard is married. He and his wife, Nancy (maiden name Shell), have two sons, John and Chris. John attended the Atlanta College of the Arts, while Chris attended Appalachain State.
Fayard is the son of the late Elam P. and Sara 
Current Focus

Key Challenges

Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1952.
Fayard earned a Bachelor's degree from the University of Alabama's College of Commerce and Business Administration in 1975. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Director, Coca-Cola Enterprises Inc. (2001-2008)
Former Director, Panamerican Beverages, Inc. 
 





